                <h1 id="foundational-cycles-the-22-arcana">Foundational Cycles: The 22 Arcana</h1>
<p>There are no spells, only engines. All stable magic is the product of a <strong>Cycle</strong>: a self-sustaining engine in the soul that loops energy through multiple <a href="/w/magic-system/glossary#sefirah-pl-sefirot">Sefirot</a> to produce an ongoing effect. Mastering this art is the foundation of the "Build Wide" philosophy.</p>
<p>This document catalogues the foundational Cycles derived from the <a href="/w/magic-system/paths/the-22-paths">22 Arcana</a>. For rare or heretical Cycles, see the supplementary text on <a href="/w/magic-system/advanced-topics/dissonant-cycles-deep-dive">Esoteric &amp; Dissonant Cycles</a>. For larger, cooperative workings, see <a href="/w/magic-system/advanced-topics/rituals-and-artifacts">Rituals &amp; Artifacts</a>.</p>
<p><strong><em>Note on the Fractured Throne:</em></strong> <em>Following the <a href="/w/library/historical-events/war-of-the-shifting-throne/overview">War of the Shifting Throne</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s1-keter">Keter</a> is no longer a unified source. Cycles involving Keter are now strongly aligned with the faction whose aspect of Keter they draw from (Law for the Concord, Life for the Garden, Balance for the Middle Pillar). This has made these Cycles more Resonant within their own philosophy but more Dissonant when combined with concepts from other Pillars.</em></p>
